WEBVTT

00:00.984 --> 00:03.335
[ Music plays ]

00:03.337 --> 00:05.987
Okay, I'm gonna say
that you like water sports,

00:05.989 --> 00:07.673
because that'll make you
10% more attractive.

00:07.675 --> 00:09.583
This is dumb. I don't need to be
on a dating app.

00:09.585 --> 00:11.493
This is a great place
to meet people.

00:11.495 --> 00:13.570
I helped a very nice woman
to her car the other night.

00:13.572 --> 00:15.497
Oh, no, we know.
The banana hoarderer.

00:15.499 --> 00:17.832
It's "hoarder."
Okay, we get it.

00:17.834 --> 00:19.259
You went to med school,
alright?

00:19.261 --> 00:21.762
Well, yes, that is the woman
I'm talking about,

00:21.764 --> 00:23.430
and...fine.

00:23.432 --> 00:25.357
Say I like water sports.
I just Googled "water sports."

00:25.359 --> 00:26.767
I think it means something
different on the apps.

00:26.769 --> 00:28.435
Ugh.
Okay, we're gonna do
the profile picture now.

00:28.437 --> 00:29.677
Yeah. Thanks.

00:29.679 --> 00:32.197
Now?
Yeah.
Let's lead with the boobs.

00:33.442 --> 00:35.016
What?
I can't believe
you're doing this.

00:35.018 --> 00:36.035
What's happening?
Ugh.

00:36.037 --> 00:37.244
Read 'em and weep.
Let's go.

00:37.946 --> 00:39.596
Huh.
Ooh.

00:39.598 --> 00:40.688
Now, what is that?

00:40.690 --> 00:43.042
Is that a nursing bra?

00:43.044 --> 00:44.526
It's my work bra!

00:44.528 --> 00:46.453
It's got support in the front
for lifting.

00:46.455 --> 00:48.363
Oh, okay.
So if you don't want someone

00:48.365 --> 00:50.457
with a moving truck,
you're gonna wanna ditch that.

00:50.459 --> 00:52.459
Here, I've got something
that'll make them pop.

00:52.461 --> 00:54.778
It's Tuesday "sex night"
with Dan, and, you know.

00:54.780 --> 00:56.555
This is the only time
it's gonna come off, so...

00:56.557 --> 00:57.872
Oh.

00:57.874 --> 01:00.059
I'll be right here,
just waiting.

01:00.061 --> 01:02.119
Here you go.
No, no, no, no, no.

01:02.121 --> 01:03.287
That doesn't go
with those pants.

01:03.289 --> 01:05.806
I don't wear underwear
in these, so...

01:05.808 --> 01:10.627
♪♪

01:10.629 --> 01:11.795
♪ Hey! ♪

01:11.797 --> 01:13.238
♪♪

01:13.240 --> 01:15.982
Sarah: Guys, there's no one
worth dating on these apps.

01:15.984 --> 01:17.467
It's like online shopping,

01:17.469 --> 01:19.394
but there's nothing
in my size or style.

01:19.396 --> 01:21.488
Well,
at least you're bi.

01:21.490 --> 01:24.399
I mean, imagine if you had
to choose from only the men.

01:24.401 --> 01:26.234
Wait a minute. Does that say
"Good Vibes Only"?

01:26.236 --> 01:28.312
Oh, God.
That's not very inclusive.

01:28.314 --> 01:29.421
Oh, okay. Here.

01:29.648 --> 01:32.165
Here's someone who doesn't
completely make me sick.

01:32.167 --> 01:33.317
Oh, yeah.

01:33.319 --> 01:34.927
You two would have
very attractive sex.

01:34.929 --> 01:35.928
Right?
Amy: Hang on.

01:35.930 --> 01:38.246
Does that say
Merrick Skateway?

01:38.248 --> 01:39.598
Look at her background.

01:39.600 --> 01:40.933
[ Gasps ] It is.

01:40.935 --> 01:43.327
She's wearing the uniform.
She works there.

01:43.329 --> 01:45.162
We have to go
check her out.

01:45.164 --> 01:47.164
And we can skate!
Amy, we can take our kids.

01:47.166 --> 01:48.515
It would be so fun.

01:48.667 --> 01:50.609
I was gonna bring them to that
booger-infested playground

01:50.611 --> 01:53.261
at the mall, but no,
I guess this is a step up.

01:53.263 --> 01:55.355
Guys, I don't even want to be
dating,

01:55.357 --> 01:57.432
much less have you as
my wingmen with your children.

01:57.434 --> 01:59.267
Mm.
But you are never gonna
find happiness

01:59.269 --> 02:00.786
if you don't
put yourself out there.

02:00.788 --> 02:03.013
It's all about
manifesting joy.

02:03.015 --> 02:04.698
Or so says<i> O Magazine.</i>

02:04.700 --> 02:06.458
Oh, crap on a stick.

02:06.460 --> 02:08.034
It's a mother
from Luke's school.

02:08.036 --> 02:10.537
Hide me, please.

02:10.539 --> 02:12.189
♪♪

02:12.191 --> 02:14.858
Oh, excuse me.
Did she just avoid<i> me?</i>

02:14.860 --> 02:16.301
The nerve!

02:16.303 --> 02:19.546
Hi!
I thought that was you!

02:19.548 --> 02:20.472
It's me.

02:20.474 --> 02:23.291
[ Both laugh awkwardly ]

02:23.293 --> 02:26.461
I just want to say
I'm sorry

02:26.463 --> 02:29.556
Luke wasn't invited
to Dylan's party.

02:29.558 --> 02:31.984
I didn't -- I didn't know
that he had a p--

02:31.986 --> 02:33.635
there was a party.
Yeah.

02:33.637 --> 02:37.047
It's just that we're encouraging
Dylan to be more authentic,

02:37.049 --> 02:39.399
and he doesn't feel like he
and Luke have a lot in common,

02:39.401 --> 02:43.162
so it would be inauthentic
to pretend they're friends.

02:43.164 --> 02:47.891
Dylan likes animals,
but not all the time.

02:47.893 --> 02:49.651
Yeah, right.
No, of course.

02:49.653 --> 02:52.229
Um, we're --
we're all grown-ups here, so...

02:52.231 --> 02:53.246
[ Both laugh ]

02:53.248 --> 02:54.898
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
No big deal.

02:54.900 --> 02:56.082
Oh, one thing, um...

02:56.084 --> 02:58.993
I want you to know
that I avoided you first.

02:58.995 --> 03:00.662
Okay, Dylan's Mom?

03:00.664 --> 03:03.665
♪♪

03:03.667 --> 03:05.926
Luke isn't getting invited
to birthday parties now.

03:05.928 --> 03:07.244
I mean, what is that?

03:07.246 --> 03:09.003
When we were kids,
we were taught to be nice.

03:09.005 --> 03:11.248
Everyone was invited,
even the losers.

03:11.250 --> 03:12.782
And we got a lifelong friendship
out of it.

03:12.784 --> 03:15.435
Yes! Who -- Wait.
Who are you talking about?

03:15.437 --> 03:18.030
Hey, hey, hey.
You got a foot in the door.

03:18.032 --> 03:19.865
[ Gasps ]
Let's all just be grateful.

03:19.867 --> 03:22.943
♪♪

03:22.945 --> 03:25.520
[ Chuckles ]

03:25.522 --> 03:27.372
Can I have one
of the new Popsicles?

03:27.374 --> 03:28.523
Depends.

03:28.525 --> 03:30.692
Who's the best mom
in the whole world?

03:30.694 --> 03:31.785
You are!
[ Laughs ]

03:31.787 --> 03:32.953
[ Cellphone ringing ]
Grocery shopping

03:32.955 --> 03:34.771
is so much more fun
when you come with --

03:34.773 --> 03:36.423
[ Screams ]

03:38.444 --> 03:39.626
Hi.

03:39.628 --> 03:41.053
Hey, Jodie.

03:41.055 --> 03:43.388
Uh, I read that Oprah article
you told me about.

03:43.390 --> 03:44.539
It is awesome.

03:44.541 --> 03:46.283
Isn't Oprah the best?
[ Grunts ]

03:46.285 --> 03:47.542
Mommy!
I want a Popsicle!

03:47.544 --> 03:48.785
<i> Yeah, totally.</i>

03:48.787 --> 03:53.065
Um, hey, so, I am working
on manifesting my joy,

03:53.067 --> 03:56.384
and there's something
that I wanted to ask you about,

03:56.386 --> 03:58.128
but, um...

03:58.130 --> 04:01.055
kind of worried that
it might be inappropriate.

04:01.057 --> 04:02.315
You can talk to me
about anything.

04:02.317 --> 04:05.135
Mommy, I want Popsicles!

04:05.137 --> 04:06.528
I want Pop--

04:07.564 --> 04:09.915
Go get it!
Sorry, that wasn't to you.

04:09.917 --> 04:10.991
[ Sighs ]

04:11.143 --> 04:12.751
Oh, man, the gym would kill me
if they knew

04:12.753 --> 04:14.586
I was asking
a client this.

04:14.588 --> 04:17.831
Can you give me advice on
starting my own fitness company?

04:17.833 --> 04:19.666
Oh.

04:19.668 --> 04:21.426
But it's gonna be more
than a company, you know?

04:21.428 --> 04:23.762
It's gonna be
a-a fitness empire --

04:23.764 --> 04:27.599
classes, supplements,
sleeveless T-shirts, you know?

04:27.601 --> 04:29.993
That all sounds great,
but why do you think I can help?

04:29.995 --> 04:31.753
Well, I mean, you used
to work at a bank.

04:31.755 --> 04:33.830
You understand money
and business.

04:33.832 --> 04:36.775
Plus, I've seen you use
the Reminders app on your phone,

04:36.777 --> 04:38.852
<i> and that is awesome.</i>

04:38.854 --> 04:40.337
Yeah,
I'm pretty awesome.

04:40.339 --> 04:42.263
Have you ever considered
taking some business courses

04:42.265 --> 04:44.932
at Nassau
Community College?

04:44.934 --> 04:46.510
I knew you would
have the answer.

04:46.512 --> 04:49.679
You always have the answer.
You are such a real grown-up.

04:49.681 --> 04:51.848
Oh, shoot.
I gotta go.

04:51.850 --> 04:54.868
Um, I got a client, but I will
talk to you later, okay?

04:54.870 --> 04:56.019
Thank you so much.

04:56.021 --> 04:57.037
Really, it was nothing.

04:57.039 --> 04:58.714
<i> Alright, bye.</i>

05:00.301 --> 05:02.634
Oy.

05:02.636 --> 05:03.693
[ Door unlocks ]

05:04.530 --> 05:06.621
Don't tell your brother
you licked those.

05:06.623 --> 05:08.698
They're tonight's dessert.

05:08.700 --> 05:10.625
Mommy's home.

05:10.627 --> 05:11.793
Hi, Mommy.
Hi, Mommy.

05:11.795 --> 05:14.629
Ooh, look, Julia.
That's your mommy, remember?

05:14.631 --> 05:16.798
Okay, I think she knows
who I am, Gloria.

05:18.393 --> 05:21.469
You're home early.
Yeah, a guy fell off
the scaffolding at the site.

05:21.471 --> 05:24.230
He'll be fine, but
we're pretending he
won't, so half day.

05:24.232 --> 05:26.158
[ Chuckles ]
Hey, Luke, guess what.

05:26.160 --> 05:29.161
You and I are gonna go
to the roller rink right now.

05:29.163 --> 05:32.664
But I want to work on this
700-piece puzzle

05:32.666 --> 05:35.058
of an African Bear.

05:35.060 --> 05:36.576
Mm-hmm, okay, okay.
So here's the thing.

05:36.578 --> 05:39.062
We're gonna have a little chat
right now, okay?

05:39.064 --> 05:40.397
Alright, I'm gonna
shoot you straight.

05:40.399 --> 05:41.823
It's time to broaden
our horizons.

05:41.825 --> 05:44.676
I mean, the animal stuff,
it's very cool, but it's a lot,

05:44.678 --> 05:46.994
and I think it alienates
the other kids.

05:46.996 --> 05:48.830
And plus, you can't go
drinking in college

05:48.832 --> 05:49.514
with African Bears,
right?

05:49.516 --> 05:50.998
Of course you can't.

05:51.018 --> 05:54.260
African Bears have been extinct
for thousands of years.

05:54.262 --> 05:55.412
Yeah, Mommy.

05:55.414 --> 05:59.006
Okay, I need you
to try to be cool, okay?

05:59.008 --> 06:00.359
I am begging you.

06:00.361 --> 06:02.176
I know you love
spending time with me,

06:02.178 --> 06:03.770
but it would mean a lot
to your mom

06:03.772 --> 06:05.105
if you went
roller skating.

06:05.107 --> 06:06.531
We'll do
the puzzle tomorrow.

06:06.533 --> 06:07.682
Okay, Gloria.

06:07.684 --> 06:09.034
Doing a great job,
buddy.

06:10.262 --> 06:11.703
I don't know
what the problem is.

06:11.705 --> 06:12.946
He's a perfect
little angel.

06:13.040 --> 06:15.765
He's not getting invited
to birthday parties, Gloria.

06:15.767 --> 06:16.708
It's their loss.

06:19.362 --> 06:22.363
Okay, we have to
fire Gloria.

06:22.365 --> 06:23.882
She's way too supportive
of Luke.

06:23.884 --> 06:25.867
We need someone
more shame-y.

06:25.869 --> 06:27.034
I think you got
that covered.

06:27.054 --> 06:28.887
What are you doing?
I'm trying to fix him, okay?

06:28.889 --> 06:30.447
This is all your fault.

06:30.449 --> 06:32.540
He gets the whole animal
obsession thing from you.

06:32.542 --> 06:33.783
I'm not obsessed.

06:33.802 --> 06:35.118
I just like them
and know everything about them.

06:35.120 --> 06:36.636
Plus, I got invited to plenty
of birthday parties.

06:36.638 --> 06:38.563
It's because you've been
handsome since birth.

06:38.565 --> 06:41.233
Yes, but also 'cause
I was so good at magic.

06:41.235 --> 06:44.127
You keep that
to yourself.
Okay.

06:44.129 --> 06:46.796
Look, I was Luke's age
when I met Coleen.

06:46.798 --> 06:49.132
He's not even gonna have
a dead friend to mourn.

06:49.134 --> 06:50.558
Don't worry, I'm sure
something tragic

06:50.560 --> 06:52.059
will happen to
someone he loves.

06:52.061 --> 06:53.912
Oh, God. I hope so.
I don't --

06:53.914 --> 06:55.229
Okay,
I'm not taking Julia,

06:55.231 --> 06:56.990
so since you're home,
thank you.

06:56.992 --> 06:58.808
Why can't we ask Gloria
to stay?

06:58.810 --> 07:01.586
Because I'm home.
Obviously.

07:01.588 --> 07:03.329
That's...
Luke!

07:03.331 --> 07:06.091
Jodie: [ Gasps ]
You guys!

07:06.093 --> 07:07.484
After all these years,

07:07.486 --> 07:09.169
it still smells like pound cake
in here.

07:09.171 --> 07:10.262
Aw, Jodie.

07:10.264 --> 07:12.989
That's old skate sweat
and carpet fungus.

07:12.991 --> 07:14.081
That is what that is.

07:14.083 --> 07:15.659
Guys, do you remember
Couples Skate?

07:15.661 --> 07:16.993
It was so hard to skate

07:16.995 --> 07:18.586
and make out at the same time,
but we did it.

07:18.588 --> 07:19.512
It was!

07:19.514 --> 07:20.755
We managed to do it.
Yeah, I didn't.

07:20.757 --> 07:22.165
That was my cue to hit
the concession stand.

07:22.334 --> 07:24.184
I used to use the licorice rope
as a microphone and lip-sync

07:24.186 --> 07:26.019
to all of the slow songs,
and then I'd eat it.

07:26.021 --> 07:27.946
[ Gasps ] Oh, my God.
It's still here.

07:27.948 --> 07:30.097
It's still here!
I was so popular.

07:30.099 --> 07:31.858
Luke really does get it
from Henry.

07:31.860 --> 07:33.026
I mean, I can't believe
Evan and Nora

07:33.028 --> 07:35.845
didn't want to come with,
but their loss.

07:35.847 --> 07:37.197
I mean, can't you just
force them to do things

07:37.199 --> 07:38.698
until they're big enough
to overpower you?

07:38.700 --> 07:39.941
Oh, no.
They're very strong

07:39.943 --> 07:41.034
from all the karate
they end up quitting.

07:41.036 --> 07:42.461
Oh.
I mean, did anyone
really like skating?

07:42.463 --> 07:44.129
I feel like it was just
the place to be.

07:44.131 --> 07:47.524
Only the losers, like,
liked skating.
True.

07:47.526 --> 07:50.360
Mom,
skating looks awesome!

07:50.362 --> 07:53.213
Aww, of course
you think so, buddy.

07:53.215 --> 07:55.122
Guys, guys, guys.
There's Seema.

07:55.124 --> 07:58.034
Okay, go rent skates,
check her out first,

07:58.036 --> 07:59.369
see if she'll murder me
in my sleep

07:59.371 --> 08:02.055
or if she's hot enough
to make it worth it, okay?

08:02.057 --> 08:04.374
Come on, Mom!
Let's get skates now!

08:04.376 --> 08:05.725
Yes, yes.
Go get skates.

08:05.727 --> 08:07.377
And, Luke,
when you're there,

08:07.379 --> 08:09.136
find out if the lady
behind the counter

08:09.138 --> 08:10.805
has a lower back tattoo.

08:10.807 --> 08:12.065
Okay!
Okay.

08:12.067 --> 08:12.899
Yeah, that is
a deal-breaker.
Great kid.

08:12.901 --> 08:13.900
He's -- He's okay.

08:13.902 --> 08:16.661
♪♪

08:20.483 --> 08:23.668
♪♪

08:23.670 --> 08:25.319
Whoa.

08:25.321 --> 08:27.488
This must be what baby penguins
feel like

08:27.490 --> 08:30.416
as they find their footing
for the first time.

08:30.418 --> 08:33.995
Or how a little boy feels
when he first learns to skate,

08:33.997 --> 08:37.423
is a more normal way
to say it.

08:37.425 --> 08:39.743
Hey, Luke.
You get my intel?

08:39.745 --> 08:41.427
Nope.
Nope?

08:41.429 --> 08:43.504
How was Seema?
Was she terrible?

08:43.506 --> 08:44.914
She was terrible.
I knew she'd be terrible.

08:44.916 --> 08:46.432
Let's go.
No, she was nice.

08:46.434 --> 08:47.526
Super friendly.

08:47.528 --> 08:49.361
That's worse than terrible.
It's boring.

08:49.363 --> 08:52.197
God, you're ridiculous.
Just go talk to her.

08:52.199 --> 08:53.698
It's a first date
at a roller rink.

08:53.700 --> 08:56.092
There's no place for
this relationship to go but up.

08:56.094 --> 08:57.869
True.
How do I look?

08:57.871 --> 08:59.520
Good. Oh, wait.
You've got a...

08:59.522 --> 09:00.613
Actually...

09:00.615 --> 09:04.209
Oh, my God.
O-Okay. Ahh! Huh. [ Sighs ]

09:04.211 --> 09:06.286
Hopefully I dry off
before I get there.

09:06.288 --> 09:07.620
Thank you.
So pretty.

09:07.622 --> 09:09.381
So pretty.

09:09.383 --> 09:10.940
Hey, ready to hit the rink
with me?

09:10.942 --> 09:12.108
Nope, definitely not.

09:12.110 --> 09:12.884
These skates were
just for optics.

09:12.886 --> 09:14.961
Cool.
I can manifest my own joy.

09:14.963 --> 09:16.296
It's gonna be
the old routine --

09:16.298 --> 09:18.372
skate, Pac-Man, slushy,
repeat.

09:18.374 --> 09:21.301
Jodie, um, you know that
if you didn't let me

09:21.303 --> 09:22.619
cheat off you
when we were younger,

09:22.621 --> 09:24.563
we probably wouldn't
be friends, right?

09:24.565 --> 09:26.565
[ Chuckles ]
You're funny.

09:26.567 --> 09:28.233
Oh.
Oh.

09:28.235 --> 09:30.051
Oh, I'm sorry, sweetie.

09:30.053 --> 09:32.312
I'll save it
for when they play ABBA.

09:32.314 --> 09:34.464
♪♪

09:34.466 --> 09:35.799
Bye, Mom!

09:35.801 --> 09:38.726
♪♪

09:38.728 --> 09:42.414
You must love that -- putting
smiles on their little faces.

09:42.416 --> 09:45.992
Uh, truthfully, not really
a big fan of kids.

09:45.994 --> 09:47.493
[ Gasps ]
Oh, I can't stand them.

09:47.495 --> 09:50.071
Dirty little germ buckets,
am I right?

09:50.073 --> 09:53.291
Do you have a pair
of unused skates?

09:53.293 --> 09:55.652
Uh, men's size 4
haven't been touched.

09:55.654 --> 09:58.263
Even the guys with that size
will lie and ask for a 10.

09:58.265 --> 09:59.598
Right.

09:59.600 --> 10:02.492
Um, full disclosure, I-I'm
actually not here to skate.

10:02.494 --> 10:05.511
Um, I saw your profile
on my dating app,

10:05.513 --> 10:08.014
and I dragged my friends down
here to check you out first.

10:08.016 --> 10:10.516
Is -- Is that weird?
Pretty weird.

10:10.518 --> 10:12.426
Too weird?

10:12.428 --> 10:14.687
I get it.
Everyone's fake on the apps.

10:14.689 --> 10:17.598
So I take it your friends
approved of me, then?

10:17.600 --> 10:20.510
They were pretty useless,
um, but, you know,

10:20.512 --> 10:22.954
I took a leap of faith,
and so far you don't disappoint.

10:22.956 --> 10:25.790
Um, but it is still early.
I haven't seen you chew.

10:25.792 --> 10:27.274
[ Laughs ]

10:27.276 --> 10:30.111
Then, uh, I guess
we should hang out.

10:30.113 --> 10:31.463
I have two bottles
of strawberry wine

10:31.465 --> 10:33.614
I confiscated
from some teenagers.

10:33.616 --> 10:36.635
Wanna get hammered
and, uh, hit the rink?

10:36.637 --> 10:40.029
Break out
the men's size 4.

10:40.031 --> 10:44.701
♪♪

10:44.703 --> 10:46.794
Rink DJ:
<i> What up, skaters?</i>

10:46.796 --> 10:49.389
<i> It's time to limbo!</i>

10:49.391 --> 10:51.799
Limbo!

10:51.801 --> 10:53.151
Whoo!

10:53.153 --> 10:57.397
<i> How low can she go?</i>

10:57.399 --> 10:58.823
<i> Nice one!</i>

10:58.825 --> 11:02.568
♪♪

11:02.570 --> 11:05.664
<i> Come on,</i>
<i> our next lucky limbo skater!</i>

11:05.666 --> 11:08.391
This does not bring me joy.

11:08.393 --> 11:11.411
Well, did you preheat
the oven, Dan?

11:11.413 --> 11:14.339
Yes, well, that's why
the pizza's cold in the middle.

11:14.341 --> 11:22.013
♪♪

11:24.667 --> 11:26.259
♪♪

11:26.261 --> 11:30.021
Oh, I'm having major flashbacks
of you during Couples Skate.

11:31.583 --> 11:34.842
At least back then I still had
hope things would get better.

11:34.844 --> 11:36.769
Could still cling
to my dreams

11:36.771 --> 11:41.032
of a husband and kids
and a house.

11:41.034 --> 11:44.536
You got all that.

11:44.538 --> 11:47.855
It's not how I imagined.

11:47.857 --> 11:50.266
I wanted
the fairytale version.

11:50.268 --> 11:52.936
I wanted my life to feel
like "Pretty in Pink."

11:52.938 --> 11:54.103
Oh, my God.
No, you didn't.

11:54.105 --> 11:55.621
First of all,
that dress was a disaster.

11:55.623 --> 11:57.290
[ Gasps ]
Redheads should not
wear pink.

11:57.292 --> 11:58.791
Who said
she could wear that?

11:58.793 --> 12:00.385
I'm saying it.
She made that dress.

12:00.387 --> 12:02.536
Yeah.
It looked like a potato sack.

12:02.538 --> 12:05.631
Okay, clearly,
you don't get it.

12:05.633 --> 12:08.709
I can't manifest joy.

12:08.711 --> 12:10.895
Nothing ever changes.

12:10.897 --> 12:12.564
Nothing ever changes.

12:12.566 --> 12:14.065
Nothing ever changes.

12:14.067 --> 12:15.400
I want to skate with Matt.
That'll never happen.

12:15.402 --> 12:17.310
That's just another
dumb fantasy.

12:17.312 --> 12:19.070
If they don't sell
licorice rope,

12:19.072 --> 12:20.888
I am burning
this place down.

12:20.890 --> 12:22.131
Ooh. [ Chuckles ]

12:22.133 --> 12:24.576
Exciting.

12:24.578 --> 12:25.818
Oh.

12:25.820 --> 12:27.136
♪ Ooo ♪

12:27.138 --> 12:28.562
♪ I just wanna get away ♪

12:28.564 --> 12:30.397
Luke: Mom, look!

12:30.399 --> 12:33.659
I'm so fast, I'm like
a peregrine falcon.

12:33.661 --> 12:34.978
Oh, that's great, Luke.

12:34.980 --> 12:38.072
Maybe just reel it
in a little bit, buddy.

12:38.074 --> 12:39.332
♪ Ooo ♪

12:39.334 --> 12:41.985
♪ We could find a better place ♪

12:41.987 --> 12:45.822
[ Laughter ]

12:45.824 --> 12:47.323
♪ Ooo ♪

12:47.325 --> 12:49.768
♪ We could find a better place ♪

12:49.770 --> 12:51.995
♪♪

12:51.997 --> 12:54.998
Okay.
Hey, hey, hey.

12:55.000 --> 12:56.107
Hey, girls.

12:56.109 --> 12:58.759
Hey.
Where do you get off?

12:58.761 --> 13:00.503
I bet you don't even know
what a peregrine falcon is.

13:00.505 --> 13:03.264
You want to know why?
'Cause you're basic.

13:03.266 --> 13:05.191
[ Scoffs ]
Whatever.

13:05.193 --> 13:06.676
♪ We could find a better place ♪

13:06.678 --> 13:08.528
♪ Better, better, better ♪
Flap away, Luke.

13:08.530 --> 13:10.288
Flap your little heart out,
buddy.

13:10.290 --> 13:12.532
Flap your little heart out.
Go.

13:12.534 --> 13:14.108
Yeah.

13:14.110 --> 13:18.855
[ Dance beat plays ]

13:18.857 --> 13:21.833
Okay, alright.
This seems like --

13:21.835 --> 13:23.359
Oof.
Oh, God.

13:23.361 --> 13:25.211
This is really wedged
in there.
Right?

13:25.213 --> 13:26.712
I think it might just be
a part of you now.

13:26.714 --> 13:28.714
Um, your profile said
you worked out,

13:28.716 --> 13:30.642
so give it a go.

13:30.644 --> 13:32.552
Okay.
Okay.

13:32.554 --> 13:34.720
[ Grunts ]

13:34.722 --> 13:36.389
Oh!

13:36.391 --> 13:39.466
[ Both laugh ]

13:39.468 --> 13:41.060
Oh, my gosh.
Ahh.

13:41.062 --> 13:43.137
[ Sighs ]

13:43.139 --> 13:45.490
You know, you should really
get this checked out.

13:45.492 --> 13:50.829
It looks like an asymmetrical
melanocytic nevus.

13:50.831 --> 13:53.389
It's got some concerning
discoloration to it, as well.

13:53.391 --> 13:55.058
Geez, you sound like
a doctor.

13:55.060 --> 13:57.560
Oh, I was. I mean,
before I was a bagger.

13:57.562 --> 13:59.653
I didn't kill anyone.
It -- It was a choice.

13:59.655 --> 14:01.005
Wow.

14:01.007 --> 14:03.508
Wow, wow.

14:03.510 --> 14:05.251
It's been
12 whole minutes

14:05.253 --> 14:07.011
and you had to stick it
in there

14:07.013 --> 14:08.071
that you're a doctor.

14:08.073 --> 14:09.255
Oh, I'm -- N-No.

14:09.257 --> 14:10.907
It's just because I saw
something, you know,

14:10.909 --> 14:12.833
possibly pre-cancerous
on your face.

14:12.835 --> 14:14.927
No, it was important
for you

14:14.929 --> 14:16.670
that I know
you're not just a bagger.

14:16.672 --> 14:20.341
And clearly, you just had
to rub it in my face.

14:20.343 --> 14:23.236
I think you might have
an inferiority complex.

14:23.238 --> 14:25.363
Oh, so you're
a psychologist now, too?

14:25.365 --> 14:27.090
Oh, no.
I was a real doctor.

14:27.092 --> 14:28.608
Wow. [ Scoffs ]

14:28.610 --> 14:31.277
I think we're done here.
I'm gonna get your shoes.

14:31.279 --> 14:32.353
Okay.

14:32.355 --> 14:34.372
Because I'm just
a shoe person.

14:34.374 --> 14:37.125
Mm, not a very good one.
These aren't mine.

14:38.378 --> 14:40.628
Wow.

14:41.289 --> 14:42.772
Yeah, right there.

14:42.774 --> 14:46.533
<i> Hey, everybody. We got</i>
<i> the reverse-skate coming up.</i>

14:46.535 --> 14:48.887
Uhhhh...Hi.

14:48.889 --> 14:50.463
You can't talk to my kid
like that!

14:50.465 --> 14:52.115
Oh, God.
I talk to all kids like that.

14:52.117 --> 14:54.375
Plus, it was your kid
who insulted my weird son,

14:54.377 --> 14:56.802
so if anyone deserves
an apology, it's me.

14:57.213 --> 14:58.955
Oh, God. I don't like
where this is going!

14:58.957 --> 15:01.290
<i> Brace yourselves,</i>
<i> party people!</i>

15:01.292 --> 15:05.386
Okay, go over here.
<i> It's time to...rewind!</i>

15:05.388 --> 15:08.072
Re-- What?
Oh, my God.

15:08.074 --> 15:09.723
Oh, my God.
Ahh!

15:09.725 --> 15:10.724
Okay, I'm sorry!

15:10.726 --> 15:13.060
♪♪

15:13.062 --> 15:15.805
[ Humming ]

15:15.807 --> 15:19.233
♪♪

15:19.235 --> 15:24.830
And we're going to get
kicked out, just like always.

15:24.832 --> 15:26.424
Amy: Okay, okay, look.
I'm sorry.

15:26.426 --> 15:27.926
Your daughter's
really great!

15:27.928 --> 15:29.318
This is all
my husband's fault.

15:29.320 --> 15:30.820
He is the one
that you want!

15:30.822 --> 15:32.155
Amy, grab on!

15:32.157 --> 15:33.914
Oh, my God,
you saved me!

15:33.916 --> 15:34.933
You feel so thin.

15:34.935 --> 15:36.826
Oh! Matt has me doing
burpees.

15:36.828 --> 15:38.995
Clearly
the gym sparks joy.

15:38.997 --> 15:40.830
Oh, my -- Excuse me.

15:40.832 --> 15:43.424
[ Gasps ]
We started a conga line!

15:43.426 --> 15:46.686
No! Get off! Get off!
I'm not into this.

15:46.688 --> 15:47.928
Aw, you're no fun.

15:47.930 --> 15:50.431
Oh, my God, you really are
a good skater.

15:50.433 --> 15:51.950
I know.
You know what, though?

15:51.952 --> 15:54.193
I was never really good
at stopping, so, uh...

15:54.195 --> 15:55.286
Wait, what do you mean?
Yeah.

15:55.288 --> 15:58.122
Save yourself.
Oh, my God!

15:58.124 --> 15:59.198
Ugh!

15:59.200 --> 16:00.708
This day just keeps
getting better.

16:01.944 --> 16:04.020
Oh, God.
Are you okay, Mommy?

16:04.022 --> 16:05.463
Yeah, no.
I meant to do all that.

16:05.465 --> 16:08.132
[ Laughter ]

16:08.134 --> 16:12.361
That's right, keep skating,
or my mom will attack you

16:12.363 --> 16:15.139
like a red-tailed hawk
eats a rabbit!

16:15.141 --> 16:17.308
Yeah!
Raarrr!

16:17.310 --> 16:19.793
Oh.
That's not
what they sound like.

16:19.795 --> 16:20.961
Okay, you need to
work with me

16:20.963 --> 16:23.147
a little bit here,
okay, buddy?

16:25.819 --> 16:28.060
♪ Yeah, let's celebrate ♪

16:28.062 --> 16:29.988
You sure you gave me
your shoes?

16:29.990 --> 16:31.564
Well, I didn't come
in socks.

16:31.566 --> 16:33.807
Wow.

16:33.809 --> 16:35.309
Hey.
Hey, guys. Let's go.

16:35.311 --> 16:36.569
Forget about your shoes.
You're never gonna find them.

16:36.571 --> 16:37.495
Oh.

16:37.497 --> 16:38.997
They can't leave
with their skates.

16:39.148 --> 16:41.332
Well, thanks to you, they also
can't leave with their shoes.

16:41.334 --> 16:42.408
Good luck
with your face.

16:42.410 --> 16:44.502
♪ It's time to laugh, to love ♪

16:44.504 --> 16:46.896
♪ To let it all go ♪
I hate you guys
for making me date.

16:46.898 --> 16:49.674
I feel like that's on Diana
for blowing up your marriage.

16:49.676 --> 16:52.585
Meh. Mating for life
is overrated.

16:52.587 --> 16:54.237
No, I think I need to lock
something down

16:54.239 --> 16:56.347
while I'm still hot.

16:56.349 --> 16:58.424
Luke. Luke!

16:58.426 --> 17:00.092
Ca-caw! Ca-caw!

17:00.094 --> 17:02.578
Time to fly the coop,
baby bird.

17:02.580 --> 17:05.097
Own it. Own it, baby bird.
You got this.

17:05.099 --> 17:06.599
♪ Yeah, let's do this ♪

17:06.601 --> 17:11.696
♪ We're gonna have a party,
gonna celebrate ♪
Aww.

17:11.698 --> 17:12.922
[ Knock on door ]

17:12.924 --> 17:15.867
[ Lila crying ]

17:15.869 --> 17:17.618
Oh.

17:20.540 --> 17:21.931
Whenever I had
a crappy day,

17:22.024 --> 17:24.267
I would come here and Coleen
would take my mind off it.

17:24.269 --> 17:27.194
Well, she's not here.
So out of habit,
I-I came by.

17:27.196 --> 17:30.790
Great. Lila's in her crib.
You guys can cry together.

17:30.792 --> 17:32.458
I'm gonna go to bed.

17:32.460 --> 17:34.443
You're not wearing
any shoes.

17:34.445 --> 17:36.612
She's teething.
Good luck.

17:36.614 --> 17:38.781
Well, if I'm gonna keep getting
in fights

17:38.783 --> 17:40.541
at the roller rink,
I have to start training.

17:40.543 --> 17:43.061
Hey, do you think I can
do Krav Maga on skates?

17:43.063 --> 17:45.454
Is that a thing?
You know what?

17:45.456 --> 17:48.791
I'm proud of you
for embracing our son,

17:48.793 --> 17:50.568
in your own bizarre way.

17:50.570 --> 17:52.128
Well, I mean,
it's just who I am now.

17:52.130 --> 17:53.963
I'm a red-tailed hawk,
so...

17:53.965 --> 17:55.222
Is that right?
Mm.

17:55.224 --> 17:56.465
Oh.

17:56.467 --> 17:59.135
Well, come here,
you winged beast.
[ Chuckles ]

17:59.137 --> 18:00.653
[ Knock on door ]
Oh, and that's a kid.

18:00.655 --> 18:02.246
Okay.
[ Door opens ]

18:03.658 --> 18:05.416
Pick a card, any card.

18:05.418 --> 18:07.159
Aww. You know
you're the reason

18:07.161 --> 18:08.235
bad things happen,
right?

18:08.237 --> 18:09.662
Are you gonna let him
do the trick?

18:09.664 --> 18:11.297
Mm-hmm.
Pick a card, Mommy.

18:12.074 --> 18:13.165
There we go.

18:13.167 --> 18:15.760
[ Siren wails in distance ]

18:15.762 --> 18:21.081
♪♪

18:21.083 --> 18:22.583
[ Car alarm chirps ]

18:22.585 --> 18:27.605
♪♪

18:27.607 --> 18:32.759
♪♪

18:32.761 --> 18:34.670
Hey!

18:34.672 --> 18:36.689
I'll give you a lift.

18:36.691 --> 18:39.283
Oh, sorry.

18:39.285 --> 18:40.676
Ignore that.

18:40.678 --> 18:42.954
Thanks. This parking lot
always gives me the creeps.

18:42.956 --> 18:45.030
Ah, you got the guns
to protect yourself.

18:45.032 --> 18:46.607
I got a spot
by the back door.

18:46.609 --> 18:48.442
It's right up next to
the dumpster, though,

18:48.444 --> 18:50.853
but you can just crawl
out on my side.

18:50.855 --> 18:54.799
♪<i> We fight and delight</i>
<i> in the tears that we cry</i> ♪

18:54.801 --> 18:56.876
♪<i> Until dawn</i> ♪

18:56.878 --> 18:58.970
♪<i> Oh, whoa</i> ♪

18:58.972 --> 19:00.196
♪<i> Hold me now</i> ♪

19:00.198 --> 19:02.531
[ Engine turns off ]
[ Sighs ]

19:02.533 --> 19:06.552
Hey, so, I have some, uh,
kind of major news.

19:07.647 --> 19:10.148
I signed up for some
of those business courses.

19:10.150 --> 19:11.798
Oh, fantastic.
Yeah.

19:11.800 --> 19:13.209
That's great news.
Yeah.

19:13.211 --> 19:14.894
I'm really glad that I came
to you about that.

19:14.896 --> 19:16.379
I mean, you're
the smartest person I know.

19:16.381 --> 19:18.230
[ Laughs ]
The smartest?

19:18.232 --> 19:20.158
Yeah.
Rea-- You think?

19:20.160 --> 19:22.218
Yeah.
Yeah, really.
Really?

19:22.220 --> 19:25.454
I, uh -- I think that you're
the total package.

19:26.741 --> 19:28.908
Thank you.

19:28.910 --> 19:31.002
That brings me joy.

19:31.004 --> 19:33.171
Um, and there's
something else

19:33.173 --> 19:35.247
that I-I've been wanting
to tell you.

19:35.249 --> 19:37.733
Um...

19:37.735 --> 19:39.660
and if I don't just say it now,
I'm -- I'm --

19:39.662 --> 19:41.345
♪<i> Go far away</i> ♪

19:43.332 --> 19:45.074
I'm very attracted
to you.

19:45.076 --> 19:47.018
♪<i> There's nowhere</i>
<i> that I'd rather be</i> ♪

19:47.020 --> 19:49.020
I think you're cute,
too.

19:49.022 --> 19:50.855
Really?

19:50.857 --> 19:54.692
Because I-I've been wanting
to kiss you for awhile now.

19:54.694 --> 19:56.861
♪<i> Whoa, warm my heart</i> ♪

19:56.863 --> 19:59.680
Oh, God.
That was inappropriate.

19:59.682 --> 20:01.607
I'm so sorr--
And you can't even get out.

20:01.609 --> 20:03.350
I-I've trapped you!
I'm a sexual predator!

20:03.352 --> 20:06.353
You're not! It's okay
'cause I'm very into it.
I'm so sorry.

20:06.355 --> 20:08.372
And it would only be
a kiss.

20:08.374 --> 20:09.874
Yeah?

20:09.876 --> 20:10.875
Well...

20:10.877 --> 20:12.359
No. No.
You're married.

20:12.361 --> 20:15.955
I mean, yes, we are
technically married,

20:15.957 --> 20:19.124
but we're not...
doing great.

20:19.126 --> 20:20.867
I'm sorry to hear that.

20:20.869 --> 20:23.963
♪<i> ...me and we're laughing,</i>
<i> we're loving it all</i> ♪

20:23.965 --> 20:25.965
Well, it's more
than just kissing.

20:25.967 --> 20:29.785
I'd really like
to do more.

20:29.787 --> 20:32.212
♪♪

20:32.214 --> 20:35.215
And that was more inappropriate,
and I'm so sorry.

20:35.217 --> 20:38.143
I-I keep -- I don't know why
I just keep just talking.

20:38.145 --> 20:39.628
Can I lose eight more pounds
first?

20:39.630 --> 20:41.630
♪<i> ...tears that we cry</i>
<i> until dawn</i> ♪

20:41.632 --> 20:43.132
Before we do more?

20:43.134 --> 20:48.637
♪ Oh, hold me now ♪

20:48.639 --> 20:51.807
♪ Whoa, warm my heart ♪

20:51.809 --> 20:53.826
Can we make it
six pounds?

20:53.828 --> 20:54.901
♪ Stay with me ♪

20:54.903 --> 20:56.312
Definitely.
Let's go do burpees.

20:56.314 --> 20:57.404
Okay.

20:57.406 --> 21:00.240
♪ Let loving start,
let loving start ♪

21:00.242 --> 21:02.818
I got it.
Okay.
I'll help you.

21:02.820 --> 21:04.595
♪<i> Whoa-oa-oa</i> ♪
